<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<br>
<b>Lnx4Win</b> stands for "Linux for Windows". It is used to install Linux on Windows partition without any partitionning step.
 It uses a linux image and swap file.
Lnx4win installs Linux-Mandrake to an image file on a hard drive and creates a desktop shortcut
that allows the user to boot from MS Windows to Mandrake.
This is not a umsdos file system, but a real ext2 file system inside an image file
mounted using a loopback device. Lnx4win also uses a swap file rather than a swap partition.
<br>Lnx4Win works <i>only</i> with new Mandrake installation procedure(<a href="../en/drakx.php3">DrakX</A>).
